Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Benjamin Ron Hulbert

records.addlTxt: ORAL NO CONTACT WITH JAH. Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Benjamin Ron Hulbert in court.  Prosecuting attorney Samuel Tyler Tabin in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Skwierawski, Branch 41.  
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.  Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant was given a referral to the Public Defender's Office. Defendant MAY be Public Defender eligible but DECLINED to be interviewed. The case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Br. 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Benjamin Ron Hulbert not in court.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 08/17/2022@2p
